[SN]TITLE[SN]
Boris Johnson defends Greenwich homes affordable quota

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
The Mayor of London Boris Johnson has defended the amount of affordable housing set for a development in south-east London.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
17 October 2014 Last updated at 17:19 BST
There are plans for more than 10,000 new homes on the Greenwich Peninsula but only a quarter of them are affordable.
He tells Karl Mercer it is an exceptional situation and has helped "get stuff moving" for London.
